00:00:11.300 --> 00:00:15.300
Herman Badillo came to New York City at the age of 10. He was an orphan.

00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:18.300
He went through our city school system, and he became a lawyer.

00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:20.300
He became a certified public accountant.

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:24.300
He became the borough president of the Bronx, the first Hispanic to do that.

00:00:24.300 --> 00:00:28.300
He became the first Puerto Rican congressman elected to the congress.

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.300
And he served in my administration as the first deputy mayor who was Hispanic.

00:00:32.300 --> 00:00:34.300
He's now running for a control room.

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:37.300
I know him. I like him. I have confidence in him.

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:40.300
We'll all be proud of him. Take my advice. Support him.

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:44.300
They're the best young musicians from around the country,

00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:50.300
and each one hopes and dreams to be chosen for the most exciting adventure of their lives.

00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:52.300
To make new friends.

00:00:53.300 --> 00:00:55.300
To study with the masters.

00:00:55.300 --> 00:00:57.300
And to play for the world.

00:00:57.300 --> 00:01:00.300
Join host Dutley Moore and guest conductor Henry Mancini

00:01:00.300 --> 00:01:03.300
for the second annual Disney's Young Musician Symphony Orchestra

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:06.300
exclusively on the Disney Channel.

